climate change
{ By Australian Associated Press   Published:  13:04, 20 February 2020   https://www.dailymail.co.uk//wires/aap/article-8024815/Key-points-Labor-climate-change-policy.html }
LABOR SETS OUT CLIMATE POLICY DIRECTION * Zero net emissions by 2050 * CSIRO says the target would result in higher wages and growth, and lower energy costs * 73 countries have already adopted it as a goal including UK, Canada, France and Germany * No use of Kyoto carryover credits to meet targets * Focus should be on clean energy, including solar, wind and hydrogen * Critical of $4 million feasibility study for coal-fired power in north Queensland - "hush money for climate sceptics" * Action needs to be taken now to avoid being affected by global trading partners imposing "carbon tariffs" * Overall aim is to achieve less than two degrees of global warming, but closer to 1.5. 
